title: An internet media company launches a plan to cover the election for Gen Z
description: Betches announces a partnership with @underthedesknews in the latest effort to take advantage of the growing role of social media in news coverage.

title: New Hampshire opens criminal probe into AI calls impersonating Biden
description: New Hampshire’s attorney general announced an investigation into a Texas-based company allegedly behind AI-generated calls impersonating President Biden.

title: Apple has quietly tripled its testing of autonomous cars, records show
description: Apple, one of the world’s most secretive companies, quietly ramps up testing of its self-driving car division as other companies face sharp public scrutiny.

title: Everyone is using the Apple Vision Pro all wrong
description: A Stanford experiment and research into headsets like the Vision Pro suggests their use should be rare -- not for daily use at home, the office or in public.

title: YouTube’s newest numbers emphasize its growing entertainment role
description: The announcement is the latest sign of growing competition not just among social media platforms but between them and more traditional entertainment outlets such as Netflix.

title: Bluesky, a trendy rival to X, finally opens to the public
description: CEO Jay Graber says the app aims to combine ease of Twitter and Threads with customizability of Mastodon. But it faces an uphill battle.

title: Taylor Swift threatens legal action against student who tracks her jet
description: Taylor Swift’s attorney said Jack Sweeney’s social media accounts tracking celebrity jets constituted “stalking and harassing behavior.”

title: Google agrees to pay $350 million settlement in security lapse case
description: A security lapse meant Google users’ data was exposed for years. Now the company is paying to settle a lawsuit stemming from the case.
